  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Staff Engineer, Product Engineering",
  "description": "<p>Your new responsibilities</p><ul><li>Own overall product yield performance and key yield metrics</li><li>Drive yield improvement, scrap reduction, and excursion management while leading root cause analysis and implement corrective actions</li><li>Prepare engineering reports, qualification documents, and yield summaries</li><li>Apply AI and data analytics to enhance yield prediction, detect process anomalies, and optimize manufacturing performance</li><li>Analyse large datasets using JMP, Minitab, Python, SQL to apply statistical methods to predict issues and improve process margins</li><li>Provide technical support and data for customer feedback and engineering reviews</li><li>Collaborate and work closely with OSAT partners, Supplier Quality Engineering and Customer Quality Engineering</li><li>Lead product qualification, reliability assessment, and risk mitigation</li><li>Mentor junior engineers and support cross-functional technical discussions</li></ul><p><br />What we look for</p><ul><li>Bachelor’s or master’s in electrical/Electronics/Materials Engineering or related field</li><li>5+ years of experience in semiconductor product or yield engineering</li><li>Strong skills in data analytics, SPC, DOE, and statistical tools (e.g., JMP, Minitab, Python, SQL Spotfire)</li><li>Experience with high-volume manufacturing and NPI processes</li><li>Strong problem-solving mindset with hands-on curiosity.</li><li>Able to drive decisions in a fast-paced, multi-site environment.</li><li>Excellent communication skills and ability to lead technical discussions.</li></ul>",
